How to build ipriv library on Unix

Prerequisites:
You should have build-essential package installed
For Java install some JDK package
For PHP install php5-dev. Instructions for PHP extension build is in php\phpipriv\phpipriv\Readme file


Linux: static
=========================================

- ./configure.sh
- make -f Makefile.linux
- make -f Makefile.linux tests


Linux: shared
=========================================

- ./configure.sh
- make -f Makefile.linux shared


Linux: Java Native Interface
=========================================

- ./configure.sh
- make -f Makefile.linux
- make -f Makefile.linux tests
- cd java
- ./configure-linux.sh
- make
- make tests


FreeBSD: static
=========================================

- ./configure.sh
- make -f Makefile.bsd
- make -f Makefile.bsd tests


FreeBSD: shared
=========================================

- ./configure.sh
- make -f Makefile.bsd shared


FreeBSD: Java Native Interface
=========================================

- ./configure.sh
- make -f Makefile.bsd
- make -f Makefile.bsd tests
- cd java
- ./configure-freebsd.sh
- make
- make tests


OpenSolaris: static
=========================================

- ./configure.sh
- gmake -f Makefile.solaris
- gmake -f Makefile.solaris tests


OpenSolaris: shared
=========================================

- ./configure.sh
- gmake -f Makefile.solaris shared


OpenSolaris: Java Native Interface
=========================================

- ./configure.sh
- gmake -f Makefile.solaris
- gmake -f Makefile.solaris tests
- cd java
- ./configure-solaris.sh
- gmake
- gmake tests


MacOS: static
=========================================

- ./configure.sh
- make -f Makefile.macos
- make -f Makefile.macos tests

MacOS: Java Native Interface
=========================================

- ./configure.sh
- make -f Makefile.macos
- make -f Makefile.macos tests
- cd java
- ./configure-macos.sh
- make
- make tests
